postcontent:
The Daisy V/L was the first production rifle for caseless ammunition. It was released in 1968 by Daisy Outdoor Products.

The V/L ammunition consisted of a .22 caliber bullet with a small cylinder of propellant on the back, and no primer. The rifle resembled a typical spring-air rifle, but the hot, high pressure air served not only to propel the projectile but also to ignite the propellant on the back of the V/L cartridge

postcontent:
FS: Excellent condition XDM 9mm 3.8 Compact, with extra accessories. This XDM is in excellent condition, only showing normal wear on the barrel. It was not used frequently for carry, so there isn't any holster wear. I estimate about 1000 rounds, maybe 1200 tops through it. This pistol is the real deal and will serve you well beside your bed or in a holster. 

The pistol comes with the original case, which includes a mag loader, mag pouch, and factory holster. Only the magazine loader was ever used. In addition, there is a N82 Tactical Pro IWB holster (most comfortable holster ever) and a leather OWB holster. Both holsters are perfect for this pistol and will be what you need to concealed carry. There are five (yes, five!) magazines included with this package deal. Three of the magazines are the extended 19 rounds magazines. These extended magazines have the medium back strap piece (different sizes can be ordered via SA). Two of the magazines are the compact 12 round magazines for easier concealed carry. Per online research this pistol, alone, is valued at over $400 well used. Add the extra magazines and holsters and you have a great deal. The holsters are also in great shape.

The terms - I am willing to meet anyone interested in purchasing this pistol at the FFL of my choice (in VA Beach). We will go inside to meet where you can inspect and subsequently purchase the firearm. If you decide to purchase the firearm I will only sell it via the FFL, who charges $20. You will be responsible for paying the $20 transfer fee. This means that you can have all of this for $520. I understand VA law does not require the use of an FFL, but I prefer to use one. 

If you live out of the area and are interested in purchasing this, we can work out a way to get it to you. My FFL will ship it to your FFL. The pistol is not legal in California or states that have magazine restrictions. You will pay the price plus actual shipping charges (my FFL will calculate - should be less than $20 ground). No Paypal, they're a bunch of commies. 

Please let me know if you have any questions! This is an AWESOME pistol. I've never had a single failure.
